The paper proposes a novel method for decomposing a partially corrupted matrix, which can be applied to many problems such as noise removal and subspace clustering. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI). Among these, machine learning and computer vision are the most likely sub-categories as they are directly related to the proposed method.
